{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PFTyfwp9Giu1pauoKBYwXH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n     2→\n     3→### Session 19 — state corruption fix #10, no-op (2026-03-27T15:16Z)\n     4→\n     5→- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and 9 previous sessions fixing this.\n     6→- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n     7→- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.\n     8→- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both files.\n     9→- Root cause: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. 10th occurrence today. This is a critical bug.\n    10→- No actual story work was done — all 74 stories are done.\n    11→\n    12→## Token Report\n    13→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    14→- By tool: Read: 6, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Bash: 1\n    15→- Files read: 4 unique, 7 total reads\n    16→- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 10th time\n    17→\n    18→### Session 18 — retrospective only (2026-03-27T14:50Z)\n    19→\n    20→- NO-OP session. All 74 stories already done.\n    21→- Ran `codeharness stats --save` to refresh cost report.\n    22→- Wrote session 17 retrospective to session-retro-2026-03-27.md.\n    23→- No state edits needed — state was already corrected in session 17.\n    24→- Total project cost: $639.78 across 4,742 API calls.\n    25→- Estimated waste from 9 state-corruption sessions: $13-18.\n    26→\n    27→## Token Report\n    28→- Total tool calls: ~8\n    29→- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 1, Bash: 2\n    30→- Files read: 4 unique\n    31→- Redundant operations: None — this session only produced the retro\n    32→\n    33→### Session 17 — state corruption fix #9 (2026-03-27T14:42Z)\n    34→\n    35→- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and 8 previous sessions fixing this.\n    36→- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n    37→- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.\n    38→- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both files.\n    39→- Root cause: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. 9th occurrence today. This is a bug in the reconciliation logic that needs to be fixed as a priority.\n    40→\n    41→## Token Report\n    42→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    43→- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1\n    44→- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n    45→- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 9th time\n    46→\n    47→### Session 16 — state corruption fix #8 (2026-03-27T14:38Z)\n    48→\n    49→- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and previous 7 sessions fixing this.\n    50→- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n    51→- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.\n    52→- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both files.\n    53→- Root cause persists: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. This is the 8th occurrence today.\n    54→\n    55→## Token Report\n    56→- Total tool calls: ~12\n    57→- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 5, Grep: 3, Glob: 1\n    58→- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n    59→- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 8th time\n    60→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"94a00213-6144-4c24-a440-4acde8467da0","uuid":"3855f2cf-2be7-46bd-adfe-b9bd24476da7","timestamp":"2026-03-27T14:50:24.044Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-27\n\n### Session 19 — state corruption fix #10, no-op (2026-03-27T15:16Z)\n\n- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and 9 previous sessions fixing this.\n- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.\n- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both files.\n- Root cause: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. 10th occurrence today. This is a critical bug.\n- No actual story work was done — all 74 stories are done.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Read: 6, Edit: 3, Grep: 1, Glob: 1, Bash: 1\n- Files read: 4 unique, 7 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 10th time\n\n### Session 18 — retrospective only (2026-03-27T14:50Z)\n\n- NO-OP session. All 74 stories already done.\n- Ran `codeharness stats --save` to refresh cost report.\n- Wrote session 17 retrospective to session-retro-2026-03-27.md.\n- No state edits needed — state was already corrected in session 17.\n- Total project cost: $639.78 across 4,742 API calls.\n- Estimated waste from 9 state-corruption sessions: $13-18.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~8\n- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 1, Bash: 2\n- Files read: 4 unique\n- Redundant operations: None — this session only produced the retro\n\n### Session 17 — state corruption fix #9 (2026-03-27T14:42Z)\n\n- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and 8 previous sessions fixing this.\n- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.\n- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both files.\n- Root cause: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. 9th occurrence today. This is a bug in the reconciliation logic that needs to be fixed as a priority.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Read: 5, Edit: 6, Grep: 2, Glob: 1\n- Files read: 4 unique, 5 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 9th time\n\n### Session 16 — state corruption fix #8 (2026-03-27T14:38Z)\n\n- Stories 16-5, 16-6, 16-7, 16-8 AGAIN at `review` in sprint-state.json despite proof docs existing and previous 7 sessions fixing this.\n- Epic-16 at `backlog` in sprint-status.yaml despite `done` in sprint-state.json epics section.\n- sprint-state.json `sprint.done` was 70, should be 74.\n- Fixed: set all 4 stories to `done`, epic-16 to `done`, sprint.done to 74 in both files.\n- Root cause persists: ralph state reconciliation keeps overwriting story statuses. This is the 8th occurrence today.\n\n## Token Report\n- Total tool calls: ~12\n- By tool: Read: 4, Edit: 5, Grep: 3, Glob: 1\n- Files read: 4 unique, 4 total reads\n- Redundant operations: Entire session is redundant — same state corruption fix applied for the 8th time\n","numLines":60,"startLine":1,"totalLines":60}}}
